items.sentence: Do you think Tom would be willing to do that for me?
Tom was evicted by his landlord for not paying rent.
This plan looks a lot like the one we had last year.
That man over there is the one whose car was stolen.
Do you know where tomorrow's meeting is going to be?
I was afraid that I might fall asleep while driving.
I only hope the rain holds off for a few more hours.
You've been driving since midnight, so let me drive.
Tom said that it took him three hours to drive here.
Tom has a driver's license, but almost never drives.
